Trace Me Internet
text:
if you know traceroute program, which basically sends packets with increasing ttl to the destination server, to know all the routers and gateways ip addresses in your way to destination server.

traceroute to google.com (142.250.77.142), 30 hops max, 60 byte packets 1 _gateway (192.168.8.124) 1.167 ms 1.356 ms 1.478 ms 2 * * * 3 56.8.48.241 (56.8.48.241) 78.082 ms 56.8.48.225 (56.8.48.225) 78.070 ms 56.8.48.189 (56.8.48.189) 78.057 ms 4 192.168.104.176 (192.168.104.176) 78.037 ms 192.168.104.172 (192.168.104.172) 77.986 ms 192.168.104.170 (192.168.104.170) 78.079 ms 5 192.168.104.173 (192.168.104.173) 97.218 ms 97.206 ms 192.168.104.175 (192.168.104.175) 102.070 ms 6 172.26.100.70 (172.26.100.70) 102.058 ms 51.193 ms 51.048 ms 7 172.26.100.82 (172.26.100.82) 51.027 ms 172.26.100.83 (172.26.100.83) 50.987 ms 51.078 ms 8 192.168.59.114 (192.168.59.114) 54.294 ms 192.168.59.112 (192.168.59.112) 70.851 ms 192.168.59.114 (192.168.59.114) 70.839 ms 9 * * * 10 * * * 11 72.14.196.126 (72.14.196.126) 46.893 ms 46.878 ms 209.85.168.26 (209.85.168.26) 56.840 ms 12 * * * 13 172.253.77.20 (172.253.77.20) 298.347 ms 142.251.55.216 (142.251.55.216) 271.334 ms 108.170.248.177 (108.170.248.177) 271.298 ms 14 maa05s16-in-f14.1e100.net (142.250.77.142) 261.361 ms 108.170.248.171 (108.170.248.171) 89.010 ms 108.170.253.121 (108.170.253.121) 83.875 ms

so i wrote a little script to take all these ip addresses, (some of them are private) in a hope to map public ip address to geo addresses in real life to get a nice path of how my packets are traveling but internet is too messy to find that..

import pygeoip import requests f = open("traceroute.txt","r")

ips = [] for line in f: for i in range(len(line)): if(line[i]=='('): ip = "" i+=1 while(line[i]!=')'): ip+=line[i] i+=1 ips.append(ip) print(ips)

gip = pygeoip.GeoIP('GeoLiteCity.dat')

for my_ip_addr in ips: res = gip.record_by_addr(my_ip_addr) try: for key, val in res.items(): print(f'{key} : {val}') except AttributeError: pass

i there a way i can find private-ip address which are most of the time not-changing despite being dynamic, to real addresses.

text:
I check this page almost every day to discover new and interesting projects and keep track of what’s happening in the open source community. Unfortunately as of today, the following message is displayed on the Trending Repositories page:

> Heads up! This Trending tab is being deprecated. Due to low usage of Trending Repositories and Trending Developers, this tab will no longer be available beginning September 30, 2022. For questions and feedback, please visit GitHub Community.
